## Limitations

The findings are based on available literature and may not encompass all perspectives on the ethical obligations of fast food companies. The reliance on educational resources and online articles may introduce bias, as these sources may not fully represent the views of industry stakeholders or consumers. Additionally, the dynamic nature of the fast food industry means that ethical practices and consumer expectations are continually evolving. Further research, including empirical studies and stakeholder interviews, would provide a more comprehensive understanding of the ethical obligations of fast food companies.